Creating a simple button click function to get familiar withÂ HTML:
The code below modifies text when a button is clicked.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Button Click Example</title>
    <script>
        function changeText() {
            document.getElementbyId("text")>innerHTML = "You clicked the button!";
        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>
  <h2 id="text">Click the button below</h2>
  <button onClick="changeText()">Click Me</button>
</body>
</html>
